  "title": "Resident Doctor/Anchor General Practitioner #81264",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Healthcare</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Resident Doctor/ Anchor General Practitioner</strong></li><li>Working Location: Clementi</li><li>Working Hours: Weekdays: 8:30am–3:00pm (evening sessions 6:00pm–9:00pm on Mon/Wed/Thu), Saturday: 8:30am–1:00pm</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic + Progressive Profit Share component</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Provide safe, high-quality, patient-centred primary care in an HSG/CHAS/MediSave-accredited clinic with good patient footfall from the surrounding neighbourhood.</li><li>Consult, assess, diagnose, and treat patients.</li><li>Manage common acute conditions (e.g., URTI, fever, minor injuries).</li><li>Provide ongoing care for chronic diseases (e.g., diabetes, hypertension, cholesterol).</li><li>Prescribe medications and arrange basic investigations when needed.</li><li>Review results and follow up with patients.</li><li>Provide preventive care (screening, vaccinations, health advice).</li><li>Refer patients to specialists/hospitals when required.</li><li>Maintain proper medical records and documentation.</li><li>Work closely with clinic staff to support smooth clinic operations and good patient service.</li><li>Comply with clinic policies and MOH/SMC/HSG guidelines.</li><li>Practise with peace of mind under company-covered malpractice insurance.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>MBBS (or equivalent recognised basic medical degree): Qualification must be registrable/recognised for medical practice in Singapore.</li><li>Fully registered with SMC: Holds full registration with the Singapore Medical Council and a valid practising certificate</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81264 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
